<div class="container">
  <h1>Computer Passwords</h1>
  <div class="content">
    <div class="text-container">
      <p>Welcome to the next lesson! In this lesson, we will cover everything you need to know about creating and managing computer passwords to keep your information secure.</p>

      <p>A <strong>password</strong> is a secret code that protects your computer and your online accounts from unauthorized access. It is important to use strong passwords to ensure your accounts and personal information remain safe.</p>

      <p>When creating a password, make sure it is at least <strong>eight characters long</strong>. Ideally, it should include a mix of <strong>uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols</strong>. For example, instead of using "password123", a better password would be "Pa$$w0rd!23".</p>
      <div class="image-container">
      <%= image_tag 'computer_passwords.png', style: 'display: block; margin: auto; max-width: 75%; height: auto;' %>
    </div>
    
      <p>Avoid using common words or easily guessed information, such as your <strong>name, birthday, or "123456"</strong>. Hackers can easily guess these kinds of passwords. Instead, use something unique and unrelated to your personal information.</p>

      <p>Itâ€™s also important to use <strong>different passwords for different accounts</strong>. This way, if one password is compromised, your other accounts will remain secure.</p>

      <p>To help you remember your passwords, consider using a <strong>password manager</strong>. A password manager is a program that securely stores all of your passwords, so you only have to remember one master password to access all of them.</p>
      <div class="image-container">
        <%= image_tag 'computer_pmanager.png', style: 'display: block; margin: auto; max-width: 50%; height: auto;' %>
      </div>
      <p>Finally, always make sure your passwords are <strong>updated regularly</strong>. Changing your passwords every few months helps keep your accounts more secure.</p>

      <p>Use the box below to test how strong your password is:</p>

      <!-- Add password strength checker here -->
      <div class="password-checker">
        <input type="text" id="passwordInput" placeholder="Enter a password" oninput="checkPasswordStrength()">
        <p id="passwordStrength"></p>
      </div>

      <p>Great job completing this lesson on computer passwords! Feel free to go back to the main modules or move on to the next lesson.</p>
      <div class="button-container">
        <a href="<%= computer_course_path %>" class="button">Back to Computer Modules</a>
        <a href="<%= computer_internet_path %>" class="button">Next Lesson</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

